stylometry: Simulation models are computer models that imitate a real life situation.  There are uncertanties in one or more variables.  Simulation models are similar to other models we have used except we use random numbers.  Some of the advantages of of simulation models are you can study the system of behavior without buidling it, its easy to use the "what if" analysis, and the results are generally accurate.  We would use simulation in a management or business situation to find results that would best help your company.  For example a supermarket may want to experiment the amount of open cash registers and the effect it will have on the customer waiting times.
